title: FruitziO Freeze Dried Fruit Snacks, Kiwi, 0.88-Ounce Pouches (Pack of 6)
description: Our Crispy Green and FruitziO product lines are created using a sophisticated freeze-drying process where water is removed from the fresh fruit in a cold (freezing) vacuum condition, leaving behind the true essence of the fruit in a light and crispy texture that’s perfect for snacking. We always let concerned customers know that we actually produce our products in China because of the quality! China is the world’s leading freeze-dried fruits and vegetables producer, both in volume and quantity, and we are involved with every step of the process…from when and where the fruit is picked to when it reaches their store. We have vigorous quality control systems in place to make sure that every product we sell meets our own high quality standards. Only qualified fruit is chosen, and the processed in freeze dried facilities that are U.S. FDA-registered and Internationally-certified (HACCP) which is a third party audit regulator. So, not only does our manufacturing process and fruit first pass these quality controls in China, but they are also routinely tested independently by FDA certified labs in the United States. Also, because Crispy Fruit is only one ingredient, it is easy for us to implement the quality control that we require, so the customer can feel confident about exactly what they are consuming!

Kinnikinnick Foods said their new breads and buns remain soft after freezing and thawing. Now you can see for yourself. FAQ Ingredients What Is Maltodextrin? Maltodextrin is made from corn. Maltodextrins are easily digestible carbohydrates made from natural corn starch. The starch is cooked, and then acid and/or enzymes are used to break the starch into smaller polymers (a process similar to that used by the body to digest carbohydrate). Generally sold as dried powders. Are polymers of dextrose (sometimes labeled glucose polymers). Do not contain significant quantities of protein, fat or fiber. Corn-based maltodextrins are not produced from and do not contain malt products. Corn-based maltodextrins are safe for patients with celiac disease since they do not contain proteins from wheat, barley, oats or rye. Maltodextrins are not known to contain MSG. Diabetics should follow the advice of their physicians. Maltodextrin's glycemic index should be considered metabolically equivalent to glucose (dextrose).What Is Inulin?Inulin, which is most commonly made from chicory, is a soluble fiber. Inulin is naturally occurring in many common fruits and vegetable including Asparagus, Banana, Chicory, Garlic, Leek, Jerusalem Artichoke and Onions.

Snack healthy with Best of All bringing natures best to you.Why Best of All Cashews are THE BEST:Roasted No salt addedCholesterol freeCertified kosherDid You Know?Cashew nuts are the edible seeds of a fruit (the cashew apple) that grows on an evergreen tree (of the Anacardium family), native to South America and India. Kidney shaped with a rich, buttery flavor and firm, crunchy texture, cashew nuts are expensive because only one nut (seed) grows per each piece of fruit on the tree. Cashew nuts are often roasted, salted and eaten as a snack, alone or in combination with other nuts and dried fruits. They are also popular in Thai, Chinese and Indian Cuisine. title: Crunchies Freeze-Dried Fruit Snack, Cinnamon Apple, 1.5-Ounce Pouch
description: Crunchies Freeze-Dried Cinnamon Apple is a mix of 100 percent real, great-tasting apple chunks and cinnamon. The only thing taken out of the fruit through Crunchies' patented freeze-drying process is water. No additives, no preservatives. That means no added sugar, no oil, no sulphur. They're wheat-free, gluten-free, and GMO-free, but rich in fiber and nutrients. Less water equals more flavor and a satisfying crunch that both kids and adults love. All this and only 31 calories per 1/2 cup! It's truly nature's ultimate snack food, and comes in a convenient resealable bag that's great for kids lunches, hiking, school, work, or any in-between meal snack on-the-go. You can also add them to pancakes, cereal, yogurt, or ice cream.Veggies can be eaten as a snack or sprinkled over your salads, soups and side dishes for added vitamins and nutrients! Crunchies Food Company was established in response to the rapid and overwhelming demand for good-tasting and truly healthy natural snacks on the market. The Company sought to develop a line of pure foods that would blend the tasty fun of potato chips, but but still be completely free of the preservatives, added sugars, trans fats and excessive sodium that are so prevalent among many snack food products. The result was an innovative breakthrough in blending great taste with important nutrition: Crunchies® freeze-dried fruits and vegetables which have proven hugely appealing to everyone from school children to seniors and from health-concious parents to busy executives.

title: Excelsior Water Crackers Cinnamon 11.85 OZ
description: These unique--fat free crackers were first produced at No. 2 Church St. Kingston in 1911, using wood-burning brick ovens, which gave them their special taste and toughness. The freshly baked crackers were sorted and packed by hand into wooden barrels. Excelsior Water Crackers were soon available in every town and village and to this day form a favorite part of the Jamaican diet. The present factory at Spanish Town Road was built in 1952, still maintaining the old type of brick ovens. Today Excelsior Water Crackers continue to be uniquely Jamaican and are made in a fully automated modern facility to the highest standards. Excelsior Water Crackers go well with all things Jamaican. Product of Jamaica.

Our seaweed snacks are made from a type of seaweed called Jarae-Kim. These are harvested in the west and southwest regions of South Korea. title: Guiltless Gourmet All Natural Blue Corn Tortilla Chips -- 7 oz
description: Why Do These Chips Taste So Darn Good?Ask any chef a delicious meal starts with the best ingredients. At Guiltless Gourmet we take gourmet seriously. Our flavors come from real food peppers, beans, chilies, cheese and spices just like you use at home.So How Can These Chips be Good for Me?Guiltless Gourmet Tortilla Chips are baked, not fried. We add just enough oil to make them crisp and help the natural flavors stick. The result is a Crispier Crunch with only 3 grams of fat per serving. Stone Grinding uses the whole corn kernel, so each helping is packed with complex carbohydrates and 2 grams of fiber. By the way, you get 18 big chips per serving, which is plenty to satisfy your crunchy craving with guiltless indulgence.Better Tasting, Better for You Could These Chips Get Any Better?You bet. Organic farmers use crop rotation, natural fertilizers and mechanical cultivation to maintain soil productivity, supply nutrients and control weeds and insects. Renewable agriculture means clean soil and water are protected and improved to grow another crop next year and the year after that.Enjoy Gourmet Without Guilt!

description: When we founded Cape Cod Potato Chips, Inc. and Chatham Village Foods, Inc. we dedicated ourselves to making the best tasting all-natural snacks in the world. title: Fig and Walnut Panforte (12.35 ounce)
description: The recipe for Panforte, literally Strong Bread in English, dates back to the 13th Century. A Tuscan specialty, Fig and Walnut Panforte is made from all-natural ingredients like almonds, chocolate, sugar, wheat flour, honey, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla. It has a heavy consistency, and a chewy, thick texture. Originally a Christmas pastry, Panforte is now enjoyed year round by Italian cuisine enthusiasts around the world.This Panforte di Siena comes from Pasticceria Marabissi, a third generation family-run business that is considered to be the most prestigious producer of true Panforte di Siena in Italy. Marabissi makes each of their panforte cakes by hand using traditional methods and the finest Italian ingredients. Their panforte has won many significant awards.Note: The bottoms of panforte are coated in wafer paper to keep them from sticking. It does not need to be pulled off of the cake prior to consumption as it is edible.

title: Gumbo File Powder (4.25 ounce)
description: Gumbo file is a seasoning made from the ground, dried leaves of the sassafras tree. This seasoning is an integral part of Creole cooking used to flavor and thicken gumbos and other Creole dishes. Gumbo file has a woodsy flavor reminiscent of root beer. File powder is said to have first been used by the Choctaw Indians from the Louisiana Bayou country.Gumbo is the Creole mainstay of New Orleans cuisine. It is a thick, stew like dish that can have any of many ingredients such as okra, tomatoes, and onions. A gumbo can have various mixtures of different types of meats or shellfish such as chicken, sausage, ham, shrimp, crab or oysters. The one ingredient that all gumbos begin with is the unmistakable dark roux. Gumbo file is used to thicken this essential dark roux and gives it the distinctive flavor.

title: Modjeskas - Caramel Marshmallows in Gift Box - Original (8 ounce)
description: What is a Modjeska? It's not a word you'll find in Webster's dictionary; it's the name of a Polish actress. Madame Helena Modjeska, famed queen of the European stage, appeared at the McCauley Theater in Louisville KY. Her theatrical performance was enthralling to a patron attending this debut, Mr. Anton Busath, owner of Busath Candies, who was honored by an introduction to the beautiful actress. He asked and was granted permission to name his confection after her. Thus the Caramel Biscuit became known as the Modjeska! This tradition is carried on today by Kentucky's own Bauer's Candy.A handmade marshmallow is at the center of each Modjeska, with a generous case of sweet caramel enrobing the delicious core. Packed in a beautiful gift box, these Modjeskas are perfect as anniversary gifts, birthdays, or just to tell someone how sweet they are to you.Available eitherplainorchocolate-coated.Varieties sold separately.9-12 pieces per 8 ounce box.

title: Lucy's Cookie Box, Chocolate, 5.5-Ounce (Pack of 4)
description: When Dr. Lucy Gibney learned her child had severe food allergies, she got down to some serious medical research in the kitchen. Inspired by her son and encouraged by her husband, she put aside her career as an emergency physician to create great tasting foods for people with modified diets. She started by taking her mother’s time tested recipes and substituted her own gluten free flour blend. Next she meticulously experimented until she baked great tasting cookies without milk, butter or eggs. Most importantly, she knew the only way to make products in a protected environment and prevent unwanted ingredients such as peanuts or tree nuts was to control the process from start to finish. She has put all of her efforts into creating a dedicated bakery where her vision is now a reality. Today, Lucy's cookies stand as proof that no one ever has to be denied a good cookie. Every crispy, crunchy Lucy's cookie is baked without wheat, gluten, milk, eggs, peanuts or tree nuts. But you'd never know it. They taste delicious. Today, Dr. Lucy continues to advocate for people with food allergies and special diets. Her vision unfolds daily with increasing demand for her yummy cookies and enthusiastic support from dedicated customers. Made from natural ingredients using no preservatives or trans-fat, and high quality ingredients are used in a carefully controlled bakery to be sure the products meet tight allergen testing criteria. Lucy’s has four classic flavors: chocolate chip, oatmeal, sugar and cinnamon. 100 to 120 calories per serving. Vegan and Kosher Pareve certified.

title: Lord Nut Levington - Mamma Mia Peanuts - 8 oz.
description: Lord Nut Levington Mamma Mia Peanuts - 8 oz. (227g) Have you ever tasted something so good you heard a symphony? Or something so spicy you could sense the fiery love that inspired the recipe? Each unique Lord Nut Levington flavor is created by the Nut himself. They are inspired by his experiences and flavor expeditions. So try them all, each is a little unexpected and all are totally tasty. Lord Nut Levington Mamma Mia Peanuts It was known as the land of opportunity - vibrant, full of flavor and the spice of life - The Big Apple. The streets were thought to be paved in gold and immigrants flooded to her welcoming shores. After braving oceans both wide and deep, Lord Nut found himself in this tasty melting pot. Upon his arrival in this bold new world, Lord Nut earned a spot in the heart and home of Mamma Sofia - a true Italian matriarch and keeper of a boarding house. Her love of life was only surpassed by her love of food. It was in her home that Nut discovered the sumptuousness that is Italian cuisine and mended his broken heart by saving someone else's. The beauty of Mamma's granddaughter, Lucia, was known throughout the five boroughs. And while chased by multiple suitors at all times, Lucia's heart was already spoken for. While visiting the local market to get the juicy tomatoes, fresh herbs and delicious cheeses necessary for Mamma's secret sauce, Lucia caught the eye of Fredo Salducci, son of one of a rival Italian families. It had been love at first sight. From that day forward, they met in secret, whispering sweet nothings and promises of a future that both knew couldn't exist. One night, while satisfying a hankering for Chinese food, Lord Nut happened upon the two lovebirds. Caught red handed, they begged Nut to keep their secret. Touched by their innocent love and having a soft spot in his heart for the star crossed due to personal experience, Nut vowed to not only keep their secret but to help them.

title: Lord Nut Levington highly seasoned Peanuts, Rebel Mary, 8-Ounce
description: Lord Nut Levington Rebel Mary Peanuts - 8 oz. (227g) Have you ever tasted something so good you heard a symphony? Or something so spicy you could sense the fiery love that inspired the recipe? Each unique Lord Nut Levington flavor is created by the Nut himself. They are inspired by his experiences and flavor expeditions. So try them all, each is a little unexpected and all are totally tasty. Lord Nut Levington Rebel Mary Peanuts There is nothing so bittersweet as a star crossed love and none so crossed as Rebel Mary and Lord Nut. Maybe it was her untamable spirit, mysterious jade green eyes or her penchant for mouth watering spice - but from the moment he saw her, Lord Nut was under her spell. Unfortunately, this love story, while hot and spicy doesn't have a happy ending. A chance encounter at an underground Blighty restaurant would bring these two flavor adventurers together. Life would tear them apart. It was a well-kept secret that this restaurant dealt in the frowned upon culinary arts. So, of course Lord Nut had to try it. He entered through a secret door using the password that of course we can't tell you. He stepped into the light, threw back his cloak and announced in a proud, defiant voice, Pardon me, I'm looking for real flavor and I hear this is the place. A sultry voice emerged from the shadows, Try the Bloody Mary, it has a kick, just like me. But, only if you think you can handle it, which I doubt. Show your face, Lord Nut shouted. I welcome a true flavor challenge and would love to see who doubts me. Rebel Mary stepped from the shadows - they both knew instantly they were meant for each other. The perfect ingredients for a spicy relationship, and a true love affair was born. In fact, it was Mary who inspired Lord Nut to start the Taste Resistance. But as all fiery things go, they can only last so long before they burn out of control. One morning Lord Nut woke to find a letter on his pillow - it was from Mary.

title: Torani Syrup, Sugar Free, English Toffee, 33.8-Oz (Pack of 3)
description: In 1925, Rinaldo and Ezilda Torre visited family in Lucca, Italy. The two returned home to their native San Francisco with something very important: handwritten recipes, which they used to create authentic flavored syrups. These syrups helped Rinaldo and Ezilda reintroduce the Italian soda to their neighborhood. Years later, our syrup was used to create the world’s first flavored latte! We’ve remained a family-owned company -- adhering to the high quality standards that Rinaldo and Ezilda set nearly 90 years ago. Each and every syrup, sauce, and smoothie is created with care and pride. That’s a promise from our entire family -- including the more than 100 members that make up the Torani team. We started with just five syrups. Today, you can use more than 100 of our naturally flavored syrups, sauces and beverage bases in coffees, sodas, teas, smoothies, cocktails and more. And we’re excited to bring you new taste traditions and flavors as we move forward.

description: Nutmeg (56 g/2.0 oz.)n(Indonesia, Trinidad)nnThe hard seed of the peach-like fruit of an evergreen tree native to the Moluccas, or Spice Islands. Use in baked goods, eggnogs, custards, cheese, egg, fish and poultry dishes, whipped cream toppings,ndoughnuts, fruits, spinach and boilednvegetables, cream soups, fruit soups, ice cream, sweet potatoes, hot milk drinks, hot alcoholic drinks, sweet doughs, muffins, coffee cakes, cakes and fruit cakes, frostings, applesauce, crpes, stewed fruits, beef, ham, and sausages.

title: Watkins All Natural Oregano
description: Oregano (18 g/0.63 oz.)n(Greece, Italy)nnA wild variety of marjoram, although a bit stronger and with a pleasant bitter undertone. Widely used in Greece and Italy, with a stronger, cruder version grown in Mexico. Best known for its use on pizza; also excellent in pasta sauces, pork, veal, fish, vegetables, dressings, gravies, seafood, poultry, grilled tomatoes and all tomato dishes, white sauces, ground beef and pork, Greek, Italian and Mexican dishes, chili, egg dishes, and salads.

title: Watkins All Natural Cumin
description: Cumin (48 g/1.6 oz.)n(Mexico, Turkey, India)nnKnown in Mexico as comino, cumin is indispensable to Mexican and Southwestern cooking, and is widely used in Indian, Middle Eastern, and North African cuisines. It is a primary ingredient of chili powder and curry powder. Excellent in cheese dishes, with rice and corn dishes such as curries or tamales; use in soups, stews, salad dressings, barbecue sauces, ground meat dishes; also good with sauerkraut, lentils, potatoes, cabbage, and dried beans of all kinds.

title: Watkins All Natural Paprika
description: Paprika (55 g/1.9 oz.)n(Spain)nnThe word paprika is Hungarian for pepper. Paprika, like cayenne pepper, is ground from dried red chiles; however, the peppers used for paprika are the mild, sweet pimiento. Watkins uses the legendary pimentn of Spain, brilliant red and sweeter than its Hungarian cousin.nUse as a garnish and flavor for creamed foods, such as deviled eggs, mayonnaise dressings, white potatoes, cauliflower, salads, dips, canapes, andnchowders. Also used as a main ingredient in Hungarian dishes, such as papriks (paprikash) and gulys (goulash).

title: Lord Nut Levington, highly seasoned Peanuts, El Cheddarales, 8-Ounce
description: Lord Nut Levington - El Cheddarales Peanuts - 8 oz. (227g) Have you ever tasted something so good you heard a symphony? Or something so spicy you could sense the fiery love that inspired the recipe? Each unique Lord Nut Levington flavor is created by the Nut himself. They are inspired by his experiences and flavor expeditions. So tryLord Nut Levington El Cheddarales Peanuts. Lord Nut Levington El Cheddarales Peanuts Legend has it that El Cheddarales came upon a beautiful village after suffering great heartbreak at the hands of a fiery beauty. Broken and looking for a way to breathe flavor back into his life, he chose the village for its bold cuisine and spice of life. He thought he had found the perfect place to mend his aching heart. Under the assumed name Sr. Cacahuete, he began his life as a quiet, wealthy landowner. But this peace was short lived. One warm August day, the ruthless General, El Desabrido, and his men happened upon the village. As was accustomed, the villagers offered the General a tasty meal - a cheesy dish made with a flavorful local pepper - the Jalepeno. Travelers came from miles around to sample the native cuisine, so it was with great pride that the people presented the General with this meal. Due to his inability to enjoy even the mildest of peppers, the General felt he was being publicly humiliated and vowed to make the village suffer for their obvious disrespect. The General and his troops enslaved the village and a ban was placed on all spicy food. All peppers were to be confiscated and any villager found harboring the fiery delicacy would be imprisoned. The peaceful people were no match for the General - except for El Cheddarales. This was just the thing he needed to breathe life back into his broken heart. He vowed to free the oppressed village and true taste. By day, he observed the General and his troops as the unassuming Sr. Cacahuete.

title: Marpro Marshmallow Candy Cones 24ct Box
description: Information about the Texture of our Marshmallow Conesnn Most of the packages for our Marshmallow Cones carry the following message:nn This candy changes with the weather. In cold, dry weather it will ben quite crisp or chewy. In warm weather it will be soft. However, crisp,n chewy or soft, this candy is fresh and tasty!nn Occasionally, we get questions from customers about the texture of theirn candy. The weather and humidity definitely affect Marshmallow Cones. Theyn usually start hard and dry, because we dry the candy in a hot room so theyn will not stick to the packing line as they are being wrapped. After then Marshmallow Cones are packed, they reach equilibrium with their environmentn and they soften. This process occurs at different speeds depending on then time of year. In the winter or in very low humidity, the texture of then candy can vary from crisp/hard to tough and chewy. In the summer or inn very high humidity, the marshmallow tends to be soft.nn We have some customers who prefer them hard (most of our employees are inn this category) and others who like them soft. To soften them during then winter you can try putting them in the microwave for a few seconds orn leaving them in a warm (preferably humid) room for a few days. However, itn is difficult to soften them in the winter time -- this is just the naturen of the candy as we still use the same recipe as when they were first maden in 1936!nn If by chance you get a hard or chewy Marshmallow Cone, it is not stale -n it just has not softened or it is a cold and/or dry time of year. And theyn are still tasty!

title: 1/2 Pound - Rare Persian Blue Diamond Salt (Stones) - Small Chunks - (Food Grade) Imported by TheSpiceLab Inc.
description: 42. Persian Blue Diamond (Coarse) - Rock Salt - Persia Salt Mill Only -- All Natural A rarity amongst salts due to its unique blue color, Persian Blue Diamond has a confident taste that gently enhances the flavor of all dishes. Oozing sophistication and steeped in luxurious tradition, Persian Blue has always been sought after, and valued for its good looks and fine taste. A very rare breed of salt that is cautious at first, but delicious when tamed. Blue salt is one of the rarest salts known to mankind, and is extracted from a salt mine in the northern province of Semman in Persia. The intriguing blue color occurs during the forming of the salt's crystalline structure, as intense pressure is exerted on the salt deposits. The individual crystals fracture the light in an unusual way and the resulting blue (which is caused by an optical illusion), becomes visible. Persian Blue has an interesting quality, in that it initially comes over as a strong salt, but almost immediately becomes milder, leaving a subtle and pleasant after taste. Persian Blue is a beautiful salt that enhances all dishes. Delicious with fois gras, truffle dishes, seafood, meat dishes. Beautiful in a salt mill as well.

description: Sahale Snacks Gourmet Gluten-Free Gift Box contains six delicious, premium, gluten-free nut and fruit blends that make the perfect holiday gift for loved ones, a hostess gift for parties this season, or an instant entertaining kit for parties you plan to host. THE SAHALE SNACKS DIFFERENCE: We stick to a simple idea: use only whole foods in their natural form, avoid highly processed and artificial ingredients, and add a dash of 'culinary magic.’ We are Certified Gluten Free – our entire facility is certified Gluten Free by the GFCO, which means we adhere to the independent organization’s high standards for Gluten Free certification. title: Oregon White Truffle Oil: The Joel Palmer House 2oz
description: Oregon White Truffle Oil, from The Joel Palmer House, is the first all-natural truffle oil produced outside of Europe. This distinctive oil is produced from white truffles foraged in Oregonand#39;s Willamette Valley at the peak of ripeness. 2 oz.

title: Oregon Truffle Oil - 2 Oz. (2 Pack)
description: From Jack Czarnecki's kitchen at the Joel Palmer House in Dayton, Oregon comes the first all-natural truffle oil ever produced in the United States. Made entirely from wild Oregon white truffles, this unique white truffle oil - with it's rich, sumptuous flavor and aroma - will enhance your personal larder with a truly unique culinary treasure. This truffle oil contains no chemicals of any kind. Hand-Crafted in small batches Jack realized that the character of these truffles was best experienced in the form of oil, a fact that Europeans have appreciated for years. His quest to reveal their elusive flavor began early in 2008. Using small batch and individually hand-crafted methods, Jack finally succeeded in producing a truffle oil which captures the essence of Oregon truffles in their ripest stage, the point just before dying when they emit their clarion call of potent odor to cause their consumption by small animals upon whom they rely to spread their spores and propogate into the future. Of all foods, truffles are the only ones that must be eaten in order to continue their existence. Jack personally chooses and sorts only the finest quality truffles for his oil. The process takes several months to produce the oil and get it to the point where it is ready to use. I was given a sample of the truffle oil on a crostini whipped with cream cheese, and was swept away in the midst of lush flavors akin to a walk in an old growth forest, a break in the middle, some spice on the back of my tongue and that ancient, legendary truffle flavor jumping throughout the finish.... - Pyreus Blog The BEST Truffle oil on the planet! We cannot thank you enough for making this delicacy available at any time of year and within our reach. Your truffle oil is aromatic, rich, dense and lush with true truffle flavor. At last! Jody and Steven Brooker Spoiled Foodaholics Chatsworth, CA

title: Marshmallow Cones-30 ct tub
description: Information about the Texture of our Marshmallow Conesnn Most of the packages for our Marshmallow Cones carry the following message:nn This candy changes with the weather. In cold, dry weather it will ben quite crisp or chewy. In warm weather it will be soft. However, crisp,n chewy or soft, this candy is fresh and tasty!nn Occasionally, we get questions from customers about the texture of theirn candy. The weather and humidity definitely affect Marshmallow Cones. Theyn usually start hard and dry, because we dry the candy in a hot room so theyn will not stick to the packing line as they are being wrapped. After then Marshmallow Cones are packed, they reach equilibrium with their environmentn and they soften. This process occurs at different speeds depending on then time of year. In the winter or in very low humidity, the texture of then candy can vary from crisp/hard to tough and chewy. In the summer or inn very high humidity, the marshmallow tends to be soft.nn We have some customers who prefer them hard (most of our employees are inn this category) and others who like them soft. To soften them during then winter you can try putting them in the microwave for a few seconds orn leaving them in a warm (preferably humid) room for a few days. However, itn is difficult to soften them in the winter time -- this is just the naturen of the candy as we still use the same recipe as when they were first maden in 1936!nn If by chance you get a hard or chewy Marshmallow Cone, it is not stale -n it just has not softened or it is a cold and/or dry time of year. And theyn are still tasty!

description: Our original Teriyaki beef jerky recipe generates a moist and Sweet product. These thick slices of tender beef are packed with the delicious combination of teriyaki and soy sauces. Some may say it's an essential component in all field MRE packs, (military acronym for meals ready to eat). Soldiers have been using MRE since the Revolutionary War and in those days they limited their rations to only one day's worth of food. Since then, with each new action of war, the content and form of MRE's have modified. Soldiers fighting the Civil War carried tinned food, but the weight of the cans was cumbersome and by WWI, the cans were replaced with lightweight preserved meats. The dried preserved meats (jerky) allowed them to carry more rations in the fields. Survivalists/Hunters and even boy scouts have jumped on the jerky bandwagon as well; keeping plenty of foods such as jerky stashed in cupboards for that rainy day. Be prepared... order NOW!

title: Persian Blue Diamond Finishing Salt (Fine Grain) - Rock Salt - in a Spice Bottle
description: 43. Persian Blue Diamond (fine) - Rock Salt - Persia Salt Mill Only -- All Natural A rarity amongst salts due to its unique blue color, Persian Blue Diamond has a confident taste that gently enhances the flavor of all dishes. Oozing sophistication and steeped in luxurious tradition, Persian Blue has always been sought after, and valued for its good looks and fine taste. A very rare breed of salt that is cautious at first, but delicious when tamed. Blue salt is one of the rarest salts known to mankind, and is extracted from a salt mine in the northern province of Semman in Persia. The intriguing blue color occurs during the forming of the salt's crystalline structure, as intense pressure is exerted on the salt deposits. The individual crystals fracture the light in an unusual way and the resulting blue (which is caused by an optical illusion), becomes visible. Persian Blue has an interesting quality, in that it initially comes over as a strong salt, but almost immediately becomes milder, leaving a subtle and pleasant after taste. Persian Blue is a beautiful salt that enhances all dishes. Delicious with fois gras, truffle dishes, seafood, meat dishes. Beautiful in a salt mill as well.

title: FruitziO Freeze Dried Fruit Snacks, Strawberries, 0.88-Ounce Pouches (Pack of 6)
description: Our Crispy Green and FruitziO product lines are created using a sophisticated freeze-drying process where water is removed from the fresh fruit in a cold (freezing) vacuum condition, leaving behind the true essence of the fruit in a light and crispy texture that’s perfect for snacking. We always let concerned customers know that we actually produce our products in China because of the quality! China is the world’s leading freeze-dried fruits and vegetables producer, both in volume and quantity, and we are involved with every step of the process…from when and where the fruit is picked to when it reaches their store. We have vigorous quality control systems in place to make sure that every product we sell meets our own high quality standards. Only qualified fruit is chosen, and the processed in freeze dried facilities that are U.S. FDA-registered and Internationally-certified (HACCP) which is a third party audit regulator. So, not only does our manufacturing process and fruit first pass these quality controls in China, but they are also routinely tested independently by FDA certified labs in the United States. Also, because Crispy Fruit is only one ingredient, it is easy for us to implement the quality control that we require, so the customer can feel confident about exactly what they are consuming!

title: Rainforest Caveman Cookies
description: Rainforest Caveman Cookies are made with ingredients that cavemen in the Amazon might have enjoyed. They are fruity and delicious with exotic rainforest flavors like Brazil nuts and cayenne pepper. There are 8 delicious Caveman Cookies per package!FAQS1. What are the ingredients of Rainforest Caveman Cookies?Rainforest Caveman Cookies are made with organic honey, almond meal, brazil nut meal, chopped almonds, dried cherries, nutmeg, and cayenne pepper. That's it! There are no other hidden ingredients.2. What kind of honey do you use?We use organic honey that is certified by True Source Honey to come only from reliable, ethical and quality sources.3. Are the cookies peanut-free?Yes! They are peanut-free and produced in a peanut-free facility.4. Are your cookies gluten-free?Yes! Our cookies are made entirely with gluten-free ingredients. While they are produced in a facility that uses wheat, we take care to protect against cross-contamination and test our products to make sure they fall well within federal guidelines.5. How long will my cookies last?Honey is a natural preservative, so our products have a shelf life of one year. However, to keep your cookies chewy and delicious, we recommend that you store them at room-temperature and in a dry location.6. What size are your cookies?Rainforest Caveman Cookies are approximately half an ounce each. Their diameter varies between 2.25 to 2.75 depending on how they spread in the oven.7. Will these cookies help me lose weight?Well, we are not going to guarantee anything, but Caveman Cookies are an excellent way to satisfy your sweet tooth while also getting protein and fiber, which help you feel full. Oh... and we also have it on good authority that cavemen had very attractive figures ;-)

description: Deano's Sea Salt Jalapeno Chips (2.25oz./63.8g): Deano's Jalapeno's are made with REAL sliced fresh Jalapeno's. Deanos Jalapenos are the newest and most unique snack food available in the universe. The Jalapeno Chip was first inspired by chef owner Doehne (aka Deano) Duckworth. After many years in the kitchen working with all kinds of hot chile peppers, it occurred to me that everyone was trying to make their potato chips taste like jalapenos. Why not just use a real jalapeno! We use the freshest jalapenos available, shipped daily from Texas and New Mexico. Our Sea Salt coating has just the right flavor to enhance the flavor of the jalapeno, which gives it a nice finish to the chip. Once again there are no potatoes used in Deanos Jalapeno Sea Salt Chips. The jalapeno chips are at what we call a medium heat level, although each batch is a little different depending on mother nature.

title: FruitziO Freeze Dried Fruit Snacks, Peaches, 0.88-Ounce Pouches (Pack of 6)
description: Our Crispy Green and FruitziO product lines are created using a sophisticated freeze-drying process where water is removed from the fresh fruit in a cold (freezing) vacuum condition, leaving behind the true essence of the fruit in a light and crispy texture that’s perfect for snacking. We always let concerned customers know that we actually produce our products in China because of the quality! China is the world’s leading freeze-dried fruits and vegetables producer, both in volume and quantity, and we are involved with every step of the process…from when and where the fruit is picked to when it reaches their store. We have vigorous quality control systems in place to make sure that every product we sell meets our own high quality standards. Only qualified fruit is chosen, and the processed in freeze dried facilities that are U.S. FDA-registered and Internationally-certified (HACCP) which is a third party audit regulator. So, not only does our manufacturing process and fruit first pass these quality controls in China, but they are also routinely tested independently by FDA certified labs in the United States. Also, because Crispy Fruit is only one ingredient, it is easy for us to implement the quality control that we require, so the customer can feel confident about exactly what they are consuming!

title: Dan's Original Beef Jerky Flavor 3.25 ounces
description: Dan's Original Beef Jerky is the best beef jerky you'll ever taste € a master piece of perfection in smoked jerky! Back in 1991, Dan's love of beef jerky and the dissatisfaction he felt with the beef jerky available brought him to a very big decision that changed his life.Dan decided he wanted to make the best beef jerky the way it was made in the early 1900's smoking and curing meat as they did back then. For many months, Dan tried every imaginable cut of meat, with countless combinations of smoke and seasonings.Finally, he arrived at the recipe that is the hallmark of Dan's jerky.Unlike other jerky manufacturers who form from miscellaneous pieces of meat, Dan's beef jerky is hand-cut from top choice beef. It is not vacuum-tumbled! Dan marinates beef in the highest quality flavorings and spices for hours in the old-style, traditional methods to assure the very best beef jerky you've ever tasted! Guaranteed!All of Dan's Smoke House products utilize topchoice beef € the exact cut of which is Dan's secret that he won't share or everyone would copy his mouth-watering jerky! It is not brisket and that's what most of beef jerky manufacturers use!Not Dan!Dan's best beef jerky is prepared in a Texas State Health Department Approved facility, utilizing TSHD preparation processes and are vacuum-sealed to assure freshness and taste.Dan's Original Beef Jerky has a mild, smoky taste that kids of all ages and adults love. Dan is proud to boast that each of his last four babies cut their teeth on his Original Beef Jerky. It's a taste you'll love to sink your teeth into as well!Dan's Original Beef Jerky is available in Dan's Original, Peppered and X-treme Hot flavors in 3.25ounce and 7 ounce packages.

Unlike most truffled cheeses, the truffle paste is infused after Moliterno has been aged so that the cheese develops its own character before the truffles are injected. Though the truffles are only visible in the veins, the truffle flavor permeates throughout the entire paste of this amazing cheese. During the aging process, oil and vinegar are applied to the cheese's rind to prevent weight loss.Once cut, the dark paste oozes out of the crevices of the cheese like trickles of water from a craggy cliff. Both delicious and intriguing visually, this cheese is a show-stopper. Enjoy this pecorino with a big, earthy Italian red with enough muscle to stand up to the truffles.Made from raw sheep's milk.Whole form of cheese is 6 pounds.We cut and wrap this item by the 1/2 pound.Please contact us if you would like to purchase the whole form.

description: Sea's Gift is the best seaweed brand made of the authentic Korean seaweed by Jayone Foods, Inc. since 2000. We manufacture our seaweed with utmost care. During the manufacturing process we check for any foreign materials three to four times before the final product is made, especially for any type of metals. Also, we regularly select random samples of the product and conduct several tests to make sure our seaweed is manufactured with the best quality. Our seaweed snacks are made from a type of seaweed called Jarae-Kim. These are harvested in the west and southwest regions of South Korea. These are the seaweed that is mostly used for roasted & seasoned seaweed. Unlike other types of seaweed, these are made with perfectly matured seaweed leaves which result in a much rich flavor. It is because of these big, mature leaves that you can find irregular holes on the seaweed snacks.

description: At Garden of Eatin', we're proud of our tradition of creating the finest in all natural snack foods. We use only highest quality organic ingredients. And each batch of chips is made to order. That's what makes Garden of Eatin' snacks so tasty. Garden of Eatin's commitment to selling organic products means understanding that all the decisions we make have consequences--all the way down to the individual farmers we buy from. We are mindful of the soil, water, biodiversity and even worker health. When Al Jacobson founded Garden of Eatin' over 25 years ago, he knew that buying organic crops from farmers who grew them without pesticides and synthetic fertilizers would be better for your health and for the environment as well. Even our oils are different. They aren't extracted chemically. We crush seeds mechanically in a press. It makes a difference you can taste. And the water. It's not just tap water from a big spigot in the manufacturing plant. It's filtered water. Clean. Clear. Fresh. Those little taste buds on your tongue will tell you right away. Imagine: All the thought and care went into these wonderful, tasty snacks. We're so proud of them. And we think you will be too.

title: White Chocolate Easter Egg - Ovo de Pascoa - Galak - Nestle - 8.45oz. (240g)
description: For the whole family celebrating Easter together. Brazilians celebrate Easter with Nestl chocolate Easter Eggs! Easter Egg milk chocolate filled with coconut and various chocolate fillings with Coconut inside. Easter - or Pscoa in Portuguese - is the most popular time to give and receive chocolate in Brazil, which is second only to the United Kingdom as the world's largest Easter egg market. What is different in Brazil is the way we display the eggs by hanging them from the ceiling. This is something which began in the 1940s and '50s after retailers found it difficult to display the eggs on shelves in an appealing way. Today in most Brazilian stores at Easter, you will find eggs hanging all over the ceiling in what we refer to in Portuguese as the 'parreira de Pscoa', or the 'vineyard'. The majority of eggs are packaged in brightly coloured foil wrapping which is gathered at the top and tied with a bow, then opens out into an eye-catching fan. With hundreds of eggs arranged together in this way, there is a real sense of excitement and celebration in stores.

title: Arrowroot Powder - 2.75 Ounce Jar
description: Arrowroot (Maranta arundinacea) is a white, easy to digest, gluten-free starch. This flavorless powder is produced from the dried rhizomes of the obedience plant. A large perennial herb indigenous to the West Indies, arrowroot was introduced by the English to most of their colonies in the tropics and today is grown in much of the world. nnArrowroot Powder is used primarily as a thickening agent for puddings, sauces, and gravy. It has twice the thickening capacity of flour and thickens at a lower temperature. Unlike flour and cornstach, arrowroot is not weakened by acidic ingredients and is is very smooth in its consistency.nnArrowroot does not mix well with dairy, forming a slimy mixture. Mix arrowroot with a cool water before adding to hot fluids. Sauces, puddings and gravies thickened with arrowroot should only be heated until the mixture thickens and removed immediately from the heat. Overheating tends to break down arrowroot's thickening property. Substitute two teaspoons of arrowroot for one tablespoon of cornstarch, or one teaspoon of arrowroot for one tablespoon of wheat flour. nnThe lack of gluten in arrowroot flour makes it increasingly useful as a replacement for wheat flour in baking. Like other pure starches, however, arrowroot is almost pure carbohydrate and devoid of protein, thus it does not equal wheat flour nutritionally.

On his first day of high school, a young man named Carl Hammond returned home and announced that he didn't need any more education. Fine, his mother replied, but you're not going to lie around the house. Go get a job. And that's just what Carl Hammond did; he got a job...as an apprentice in a candy factory. In 1920, after several years of learning the candy business, Carl T. Hammond, Sr. founded Hammond's Candy Company in Denver, Colorado. Over the past 90 years, the Mile High City has seen a number of fine chocolate and candy manufacturers come and go, but one special company is still very much in business. Hammond's Candies still honors Carl's motto, Nothing is more important that quality.

title: Sunfood Cashews, Whole, Certified Organic, Non-GMO Verified, Vegan, Raw, 16oz
description: Did you know that most cashews that say they are raw are not really raw at all? Cashews are typically extracted using steam or high heat because the kernel is surrounded by a sticky resin. How do people get away with calling them raw? There is a loophole; since the nuts have not been roasted after they were extracted they are considered raw by the commercial nut industry. But we have gone to great lengths to bring you a truly raw cashew.nnOur cashews are organically grown and then hand cracked using a specially designed tool to remove the kernel. This leaves the nutrients and enzymes intact, as nature intended. Raw cashews are naturally high in beautifying oleic acid and also contain magnesium, manganese, selenium and zinc. Zinc is a critical mineral for enzyme formation and reproductive health, making raw, organic cashews a very valuable food.nnHigh in protein and great for any time you need a quick boost of natural energy, Sunfood Whole Raw Cashews are the perfect snack for any time. Originally native to Brazil and brought to Southeast Asia in the 1500's, cashews have long been revered for their healthy fats and antioxidant properties. With a delicious, creamy flavor that is versatile enough to be used in a variety of dishes, you will love these raw, organic cashews.

title: Christmas Wafers - Oplatki, Set of 3
description: A part of the Polish family Christmas Tradition is the breaking the Christmas Wafer (Oplatekin Polish pronouncedoh-pwah-tek) during the Christmas Eve Vigil Feast orWigilia, the holiest of all the nights of the year in the Polish home, as their ancestors before them have done during the Christmas Celebration uniting the past with the present… heaven with earth.The sacred wafers, much like those used for Holy Communion (unleavened wafers baked from pure wheat flour and water), are shared with each person present. Family members and friends break off a piece ofoplatekand give it to one another to eat. During the exchange best wishes and blessing are expressed as well as forgiveness. The breaking and exchanging part ofoplatekis intend to remind participants of the importance of Christmas, God, and family. This is the most emotional time of the holiday for the Polish family-the sharing expression of love and forgiveness in celebration and tradition.The Vigil revolves around the importance of the Christmas Wafer. It literally unites family wherever they are on the Earth. Christmas Wafers have been mailed to each other during the holy season to solidify family unity. Send a package ofoplatkito a loved one today to continue sharing this yearly ritual and rich heritage.The set of three packaged Christmas Wafers (plural:Oplatki) are hygienically sealed in polybags with a varying color image on the front of the package. Also, each wafer has a different nativity theme image on the front. Wafers are wrapped in a booklet that contains a varying prayer, christmas carol and religious blessing in Polish language. title: Popchip - Potato Chips All Natural Sweet Potato - 3 oz.
description: Popchips Potato Chips Sweet Potato - 3 oz. (85g)Popchips Potato Chips Sweet Potato are sweet, crispy, and a lot of delicious. Lately all this low-fat health talk has been taking the fun right out of snacking, not to mention the falvor, so we found a new way to put it back into an all natural chip like you've never tasted before. They start with sweet potatoes and other all-natural ingredients, add a little heat and pressure, and *POP* it's a chip! Then they use the finest seasonings for a snack so tasty and crispy, you won't even notice it's healthier. No preservatives No artificial flavors or colors No cholesterol 0 grams of saturated fat 0 grams of trans fat Vegan Gluten free What are Popchips? How They PopNaturally delicious and healthier. That's popchips. When they said it couldn't be done, they raised the snack bar. How do they do it? Well, first, let's talk about how they don't do it. They never fry their chips. That just puts a lot of stuff in there that they could all do without. They never bake their chips either. That just takes a lot of flavor out, which, as snackers, they simply can't do without. So they came up with a chip like no snack aisle has seen (or taste bud has tasted). Thanks to the magic of popping, they found a way to pop all the flavor in, while keeping fake stuff and at least half the fat of regular flavored chips out. The Magic of PoppingPopping is a way of making their naturally delicious chips. They start with the finest ingredients, add a little heat and pressure, and pop! It's a chip. All that's added is a flavorful blend of seasonings to create taste-bud popping flavors that appeal to the whole family. Pop open a bag of popchips and try for yourself. Everybody has a favorite. Or two. Naturally Delicious. Nothing Fake or Phony.Their pledge: no fake colors, no fake flavors, no preservatives, no fluorescent orange fingertips, and no wiping your greasy chip hand on your jeans. No, really.
